WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.240
Floor to standing desks are seriously niche, but&nbsp;
they basically do what a regular standing desk&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:05.240 --> 00:00:11.520
can do, and then some. Think of them as&nbsp;
standing desk plus. In the last couple of years,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:16.200
we've tried and tested what are possibly&nbsp;
the only two real contenders for a full-time&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:21.640
floor to standing desk. And today, we'll pit&nbsp;
them against each other for a showdown of epic&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:21.640 --> 00:00:28.800
proportions. In one corner, we have the vanguard&nbsp;
of this space, the Lowdesk Pro, formerly known as&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:35.520
Uppeal. And in the opposite corner, we have the&nbsp;
new challenger, the Flow Desk from marinamantra.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:41.080
Lowdesk versus Flow Desk. Who will come out&nbsp;
on top in this contest? Let the battle begin.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:42.280 --> 00:00:48.480
First, let's consider design from an aesthetic&nbsp;
point of view. The Lowdesk Pro looks familiar&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:53.520
and recognizable. It's close to how you&nbsp;
would imagine a standing desk to look like.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:58.760
There's a bit of that practical, heavy&nbsp;
machinery aesthetic to it. It doesn't offend,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:58.760 --> 00:01:04.280
but it doesn't stand out either. Obviously,&nbsp;
looks are subjective, but in our opinion,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:10.640
the Flow Desk has a visually more refined and&nbsp;
cohesive design. There are less hard edges,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:16.680
and the wooden tabletop paired with gray felt&nbsp;
covers give it more of a warm and considered vibe.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:22.920
Now that said, this cohesive design comes at a&nbsp;
small cost. At the moment, the Flow Desk&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:29.280
is not customizable. It comes in one size, two&nbsp;
different colors, and you can't just order the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:33.920
legs and slap your own tabletop&nbsp;
on it. With the Lowdesk Pro, you could.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:33.920 --> 00:01:39.360
If you don't like their tabletop options&nbsp;
from laminated tabletops to bamboo and wood,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:39.360 --> 00:01:44.080
then just get the legs and complete&nbsp;
the desk with your own. In fact, if you're&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:50.400
outside of the US, you might just have to do that.&nbsp;
Because, as of the last update we heard, Lowdesk no&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:50.400 --> 00:01:56.760
longer ships tabletops internationally. So, that&nbsp;
could be a pro or a con depending on your needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:56.760 --> 00:02:03.000
When it comes to extras, though, the Flow Desk&nbsp;
fights back. The gray felt covers hide cables,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:08.680
and there's also a built-in tray at the&nbsp;
back to manage power strips and additional cables.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:08.680 --> 00:02:14.160
Although it's not the most spacious and
could be a bit of a tight fit if you have bulkier&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:14.160 --> 00:02:20.280
power bricks. With the Lowdesk Pro, we had&nbsp;
to purchase and install our own cable tray.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:25.800
We didn't spend too much time organizing the&nbsp;
cables perfectly, which is why we usually try&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:25.800 --> 00:02:30.800
to avoid filming the underside of the desk.&nbsp;
We don't have to do that with the Flow Desk.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:36.440
So, if you're obsessed with having immaculate&nbsp;
cable management, then you'll most certainly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:36.440 --> 00:02:42.720
be happier looking at the underside of the Flow&nbsp;
Desk compared to the Lowdesk Pro. One of the main&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:48.200
inconvenience of the X-frame style legs of the&nbsp;
Flow Desk is that there's less leg room&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:53.680
compared to traditional straight column legs.&nbsp;
This is especially true when the desk is at the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:58.320
lower settings and you won't be able to stretch&nbsp;
or straighten out your legs in front of you.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:58.320 --> 00:03:03.840
You won't have the issue with the Lowdesk&nbsp;
Pro. So if you like to sit with outstretched legs,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:09.840
then this is definitely something to consider.&nbsp;
However, the X-frame style legs is what allows&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:16.200
the Flow Desk to go lower than the Lowdesk Pro,&nbsp;
which is important if your primary objective is to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:22.360
use it as a floor desk. Both of these options&nbsp;
have a similar amount of travel. We measured&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:22.360 --> 00:03:30.040
82 cm with the Flow Desk and 80 cm with the Lowdesk Pro. While it may just be a 2 cm difference,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:30.040 --> 00:03:36.360
the Flow Desk can actually go 5 cm lower than&nbsp;
the Lowdesk Pro. If you're of average height,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:36.360 --> 00:03:42.200
this could be the difference between the desk&nbsp;
being usable or not usable without a floor seat.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:48.080
In our case, the Flow Desk is borderline&nbsp;
usable for us without a floor seat, whereas we&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:53.560
wouldn't want to use the Lowdesk Pro&nbsp;
without one. It is rare for us to sit at our desk&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:59.360
without an elevated floor cushion, so this is not&nbsp;
a deal breaker, but a lower minimum height is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:04.240
nice to have and could be the difference&nbsp;
maker for some. If what you're more concerned&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:10.360
about is speed, then you may want to know that the&nbsp;
Lowdesk Pro is quite a bit faster than the Flow&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:10.360 --> 00:04:17.320
Desk. On top of moving vertically, the legs on the&nbsp;
Flow Desk move laterally as well, so some speed is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:23.360
lost there. Here you can see a comparison of the&nbsp;
two desks moving the same travel distance with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:30.200
a lighter setup on the Flow Desk, no less, but&nbsp;
still, it's about 35% slower than the Lowdesk Pro.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:30.200 --> 00:04:35.040
Frankly speaking, we've never been bothered by&nbsp;
how long it takes either of these desks to go&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:35.040 --> 00:04:40.720
up and down. But we can understand how some people&nbsp;
may not want or have the patience to wait for that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:47.240
extra few seconds whenever adjusting the&nbsp;
desk. But with speed comes noise. The Lowdesk Pro&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:47.240 --> 00:04:53.480
did surprise us a little with the motor noise the&nbsp;
first time we used it. It's not obnoxiously loud,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:53.480 --> 00:04:57.960
but because we were trying a standing desk&nbsp;
in a quiet environment for the first time,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:03.840
the noise was something that stood up. It doesn't&nbsp;
bother us in subsequent day-to-day use, it's just&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:09.400
something we observed. The Flow Desk, on the other&nbsp;
hand, also surprised us in the noise department,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:09.400 --> 00:05:15.360
but in a completely different way. It is super&nbsp;
quiet. At the bottom of his operational height,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:15.360 --> 00:05:21.120
the desk is practically silent. When our fans&nbsp;
are running and there are cars going by outside,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:26.560
we can barely hear the desk moving. As it&nbsp;
enters the upper half of its operational range,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:31.520
the volume gets a tiny bit louder, but you&nbsp;
have to be paying attention to hear it.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:38.120
So, the Flow Desk sounds as gentle and refined&nbsp;
as it looks. When it comes to stability,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:38.120 --> 00:05:43.880
it may not be a huge difference, but the&nbsp;
difference is there. The Lowdesk Pro feels slightly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:43.880 --> 00:05:50.240
more stable throughout its entire operating range.&nbsp;
It's rock solid at lower settings, and as&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:50.240 --> 00:05:56.480
it gets higher, it understandably loses some of&nbsp;
that stability. The Flow Desk actually feels like&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:56.480 --> 00:06:02.400
it maintains it stability a bit better going&nbsp;
from floor desk to standing desk. The issue is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:02.400 --> 00:06:08.080
it's already not as rock solid starting from the&nbsp;
lower settings compared to the Lowesk Pro, which&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:08.080 --> 00:06:13.720
makes us wonder if any instability we experienced&nbsp;
with the Flow Desk might have something to do with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:13.720 --> 00:06:19.000
the lack of micro adjustments on the desk feet&nbsp;
to negate the effects of uneven floors.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:25.280
So, a bit of a wasted opportunity. Still, both&nbsp;
desks are stable enough for what we use them for,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:31.720
but we have to give the edge to the Lowdesk Pro.&nbsp;
And lastly, let's compare price and availability.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:32.240 --> 00:06:40.800
As of this video, the Flow Desk is priced at&nbsp;
USD 1049, while the Lowdesk Pro starts at USD 1300&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:41.480 --> 00:06:49.400
with a laminate tabletop, USD 1400 with a bamboo&nbsp;
tabletop, and up to USD 1900 for one with a wooden&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:55.520
tabletop. In short, the Flow Desk is&nbsp;
the more affordable option. Both offer free&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:55.520 --> 00:07:00.960
shipping for customers in the US. And as of the&nbsp;
last update we received, marinamantra doesn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:07.320
ship internationally, while Lowdesk does, at least&nbsp;
for the desk legs, although international shipping&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:13.080
could be quite costly. Ultimately, there isn't&nbsp;
a clear winner in this contest. The question is,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:13.080 --> 00:07:19.280
what do you value more? The Flow Desk subjectively&nbsp;
looks nicer, and has a couple more thoughtful&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:19.280 --> 00:07:24.880
design elements and useful accessories. It&nbsp;
goes lower and has a tiny bit more range.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:32.360
It's much quieter, and is also more affordable.&nbsp;
The Lowdesk Pro is more customizable. You can get&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:38.920
just the desk legs if you want. There is&nbsp;
more leg room, it's faster, and it feels slightly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:43.960
more stable. If you're looking for a floor&nbsp;
to standing desk, either of these could work,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:43.960 --> 00:07:49.280
but depending on your specific needs, you may want&nbsp;
to pick one over the other. What we've covered are&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:49.280 --> 00:07:54.560
the key differences between the two desks, but&nbsp;
we also have a written article which we'll keep&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:54.560 --> 00:08:00.280
updating along the way with additional information&nbsp;
we may have missed in this video. So check that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:00.280 --> 00:08:05.844
out if you like and tell us, which of these two&nbsp;
floor to standing desks would you choose.

